      <title>1849 Jun. 27, Gallatin, Tennessee [to] [Adam] Fergusson / Jas. T. Crary</title>
   </titleInfo>
   <abstract>This is a letter from Jas T. Crary to Adam Fergusson, dated June 27, 1849. Crary writes about politics in Tennessee. He mentions General Trousdale. He writes that cholera has hit Gallatin very hard. He writes that he wanted to visit Carthage but could not leave his school. He wants Fergusson to write him with a summary of the speeches that he missed.</abstract>
